Leicester City midfielder, Wilfred Ndidi, is now on Real Madrid’s summer shopping list, according to Mundo Deportivo. It is understood that Real see the Super Eagles star, as an alternative to Rennes youngster Eduardo Camavinga. The LaLiga giants are not happy with Rennes’ €75m valuation for Camavinga and are now looking at other players. Ndidi has emerged as a top alternative, although he has a contract with the Premier League club until 2024. The 23-year-old joined Leicester in 2017 from Genk for £15million is valued at around £45-50m. Real boss, Zinedine Zidane, will be in the market for a midfielder, who can act as a cover for Casemiro. EPL: What Brendan Rodgers said about Ndidi's quality ahead of Leicester with West Ham clash Ndidi addresses comparison between himself, Chelsea’s N’Golo Kante Ogu ready to give up salary to play with Ndidi